    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-04-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-04-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="820"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d820">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">703.5492/18: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-04-15">April 15,
                            1942</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>948. Your 1420, 9th.<note n="47" xml:id="d820fn47">Not printed.</note> Inform
                    Thai Government that limitation of written and oral communication between Swiss
                    representative and American Legation Bangkok and refusal by Thai-Japanese mixed
                    committee of permission for American official group to retain sufficient
                    domestic servants necessary under prevailing climatic conditions for adequate
                    maintenance of health do not correspond to favorable treatment accorded Japanese
                    officials in United States (Thai officials are of course completely at liberty)
                    and that this Government expects the removal of these inequalities in treatment
                    of American officials in Thailand.</p>
                <p>Japanese Government should be informed of foregoing with statement this
                    Government wishes instructions to be issued to Japanese officials in Thailand to
                    work for desired improvement in situation of American officials there.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
